        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 2:10PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 210 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ladonia, or 8 miles southwest of Smiths, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Phenix City, Smiths, Smiths Station, Ladonia, Bibb City, Goat Rock
Lake, Monterey Heights, Ladonia Sports Complex, Phenix Drag Strip,
and Parkmanville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
